From: 
To:  >, (USANYS)" 
Subject: FW: Request re Maxwell Relativity 
Date: Tue, 08 Dec 2020 21:46:21 +0000 
lane-Images: image002.jpg 
As we discussed on our call with and on Friday, my understanding is that the FBI has ceased reviewing all 
content from Epstein's devices and will limit their review of the devices to (a) documents tagged Responsive on Relativity, 
(b) images and videos identified as Responsive during the review conducted by the FBI and SDNY this fall, and (c) portions 
of iPads and the iPhone that SDNY identified responsive during our review this fall. 
We should plan to do the same going forward. If you guys encounter anything that appears to come from any of Epstein's 
devices that you believe was not identified responsive, please let me know, and we can take action to confirm and lock off 
any nonresponsive material from review. 
From: (USANYS) [Contractor] 
Sent: Tuesday, December 8, 202010:07 AM

To: (USANYS) [Contractor] <II> 
(USANYS) 
Subject: Request re Maxwell Relativity 
EFTA00011251

Now that we have completed our responsiveness review in the "US v Epstein (SW Returns)" database, we need to lock off 
access to any non-responsive materials in that database. Would it be possible to please lock off access to the 397,365 
documents in that database that are NOT currently tagged "Identified Responsive"? That should leave just the 1,218,719 
documents that are tagged "Identified Responsive" accessible to the team for use in our case. 
Happy to have a call to discuss if that would be useful. 
Thanks very much, 
EFTA00011252
